The Governor of Imo State, Senator Hope Uzodinma has berated protesters who took to the streets and stressed that they acted ignorantly and were not abreast with the instant law of the land. According to the Governor, the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, took undue advantage of the ignorance of the citizenry to protest against his victory at the Supreme Court. The governor who spoke through his spokesman, Oguike Nwachukwu, faulted the protest as superfluous. He stressed that following the judgement by the Supreme Court, PDP members had sent congratulatory messages. While indicating that those masterminding the protest does not wish the state well and are bent on not seeing anything good in the APC administration. His worlds,  “I don’t know why  these people behind the protest allow their children who are based abroad to come and lead the protest, they want to endanger the lives of ordinary citizens. I advise parents to warn their children from taking part in such protest, which sometimes degenerates into violence. Why should they take advantage of the ignorant ones, they have their rights to protest, but they should do it within the ambit of the law,” Uzodinma said. Speaking, the Imo State chairman of APC, Barrister, Marcillinus Nlemigbo, described the protest by PDP as a fruitless venture, wondering why the APC did not stage a protest when Hon. Emeka Ihedioha won. “They shouldn’t have been a protest, when Ihedioha won, did we protested? Why are they protesting when the pronouncement by the Supreme Court is clear, this people should not turn this state to a place of lawlessness”.